title: India Technology News: Absolute Security Announces Plans to Expand Presence in India
summary: Absolute Security, a global provider of cybersecurity solutions, plans to expand its presence in India. The company aims to strengthen its foothold in the Indian market and provide enhanced security services to local businesses. Absolute Software's expansion in India is expected to create new job opportunities and contribute to the country's growing cybersecurity industry.

title: India Develops First Indigenous Antibiotic, Nafithromycin, Says Union Science and Tech Min Dr Jitendra Singh
summary: India has developed its first indigenous antibiotic, Nafithromycin, said Union Science and Technology Minister Dr Jitendra Singh. The development is a significant milestone in the country's efforts to reduce dependence on foreign-made antibiotics. The new antibiotic is expected to be a game-changer in the fight against antibiotic-resistant bacteria.

title: Taiwan seeks bigger tech presence in India as U.S. demand rises, trade body chief says
summary: Taiwan is looking to increase its presence in India's tech sector as demand from the US rises, according to the trade body chief. The move is seen as an opportunity for Taiwan to diversify its exports and reduce dependence on the US market. Taiwan's tech industry is expected to benefit from India's growing demand for electronics and semiconductors.
